1. Heating and Hot Water Costs

The heating and hot water costs invoiced correspond to the actual expenses directly related to the use of the heating system and the central hot water system.
They include in particular the following expenses:
- the fuels and energy used;
- the electricity necessary for the operation of the burners and pumps;
- the costs of using alternative energies;
- the cleaning of the heating system and the chimney, the scraping, the burning and the greasing of the boiler as well as the disposal of waste and slag;
- the periodic inspection of the heating system, including oil tanks, and the descaling of the hot water system, water heaters and pipes;
- the reading, accounting and maintenance of the necessary devices when the heating costs are calculated on an individual basis;
- the maintenance;
- the insurance premiums that relate exclusively to the heating system;
- the administrative work necessary for the use of the heating system.
The maintenance and administrative costs may be calculated on the basis of the actual expenses or invoiced up to the usual rates.
Expenses related to ordinary maintenance (repairs), renewal as well as interest and depreciation of the installations cannot be included in the heating costs and service charges.

2. Service Charge Accounting

The service charge accounting must be carried out within a maximum period of six months from the set date. If the lessor does not carry out the service charge accounting within this period, the tenant may request the reimbursement of the advance payments he/she has made after having notified the lessor in writing.

